<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>My Life in Weeks</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/tippy.js@6/dist/tippy.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.bunny.net">
  <link href="https://fonts.bunny.net/css?family=dm-mono:400|dynapuff:700" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <img src="/images/drawing.svg" alt="Drawing of human figure stooped over and reaching for an hourglass; some abstract shapes and a gridded sheet of paper surround them" width="866" height="468">
  <article class="flow">
    <header class="flow">
      <h1 id="pageTitle">My Life in Weeks</h1>
      <p>Ah, yes, I do love a combination data visualization/mortality reminder. Each box on this grid represents one week of my life. It is interspersed with events and situations. (Although... as I filled this out, I began to feel a bit squeamish in a privacy/overexposure way. So right now this is an odd mixture of pivotal world events and places where I lived and worked. ðŸ¤·)</p>
      <p>A few implementations of this concept have popped up on the internet recently. Itâ€™s based on <a href="https://waitbutwhy.com/2014/05/life-weeks.html">a 2014 post by Tim Urban at Wait But Why</a> that presented some interesting ways to visualize your finitude. Then <a href="https://busterbenson.com/life-in-weeks">Buster Benson made one</a>. Most recently, I came across <a href="https://weeks.ginatrapani.org/">a version by Gina Trapani</a>.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="life-weeks-table" style="--flow-space: 2em;">
      {% for week in lifeInWeeks %}
        {# Set tooltips #}
        {% set tooltip = "Week " ~ (week.index) ~ " / " ~ week.date %}

        {% if week.events.length %}
          {% set tooltip = tooltip + "<br>" %}
          {% for event in week.events %}
            {% set tooltip = tooltip + event.icon + " " + event.title %}
            {% if not loop.last %}{% set tooltip = tooltip + "<br>" %}{% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        {% endif %}

        {% if week.timespans.length %}
          {% set tooltip = tooltip + "<br>" %}
          {% for span in week.timespans %}
            {% set tooltip = tooltip + span.icon + " " + span.title %}
            {% if not loop.last %}{% set tooltip = tooltip + "<br>" %}{% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        {% endif %}

        <div
          class="week-box{% if week.isPast %} past{% endif %}"
          data-tippy-content="{{ tooltip | safe }}"
          tabindex="0"
        >
          {% for event in week.events %}
            {% if not event.hide_from_grid %}
              <span class="event-icon">{{ event.icon }}</span>
              <span class="event-title">{{ event.title }}</span>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </article>

  <script src="https://unpkg.com/@popperjs/core@2"></script>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/tippy.js@6"></script>
  <script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
      tippy('.week-box', {
        allowHTML: true,
        placement: 'top',
        theme: 'light-border',
      });
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>